# Galadriel execution rules

`AGENTS.md` is the primary repository instruction file.
Read it before you act.
Read `RELEASE-POLICY.md` before release work.
Read `release/0.9.0/RELEASE-RUNBOOK.md` before qualification or publication.

## Start each task

Work from the repository root.
Record the exact commit and tree.
Inspect the worktree before you edit.
Read the applicable code, tests, schema, and documentation.
Check for concurrent work on each file.
Preserve unrelated changes.

Stop before an edit that conflicts with another owner.

## Non-negotiable boundary

Galadriel reports advisory evidence only.
Galadriel MUST NOT grant or widen authority.
`Nominal` MUST NOT create permission.
Missing or incompatible evidence MUST NOT become `Nominal`.
Invalid input or invalid configuration MUST return an error.

Keep PID and NCP integrations off by default.
Keep the PID path additive.
PID evidence MUST NOT repair a failed core prerequisite.
Keep all Rust targets free of unsafe code.
Bind cross-channel input to one track and one exact sequence.
Bind it to a common projection and physical frame.

Bind live input to its session, producer, epoch, route, and lifecycle.
Bound resources before expensive work.
Preserve abstention and negative results.

## Release identity

The current release version is `0.9.0`.
Sepehr Mahmoudian is the author.
The canonical GitHub owner is `sepahead`.
Keep every workspace package at `publish = false`.
Do not add a project DOI or Zenodo record.
Do not claim production support or deployment qualification.

Each tracked edit creates a new candidate identity.
Rerun candidate-bound verification after each tracked edit.
Do not reuse evidence from an earlier candidate.
Do not modify a signed evidence file.
Do not overwrite an evidence directory.

## Protected records

Do not edit a file in the protected-record list in `AGENTS.md`.
Do not hand-edit a generated artifact.
Change its declared generator.
Do not rewrite contract, fixture, schema, or evidence JSON as style work.

## Change method

Use `rg` for search.
Use `apply_patch` for manual edits.
Do not use destructive Git commands.
Do not weaken a guard to make a test pass.
Add a negative test for each new accept path.
Add a positive test for each new fail-closed path.

Test feature-disabled behavior when an optional feature changes.

Treat external model output as advisory review.
Do not treat that output as release evidence.
Do not let an external model decide a security or authority boundary.
Verify each suggestion against code, tests, and retained evidence.

## Secrets

Keep `.env` ignored.
Do not print a secret value.
Do not put a secret in a command argument.
Do not put a secret in a prompt, log, commit, document, or evidence file.
Pass an approved secret through the process environment.
Stop if output contains a secret.

Rotate an exposed credential before you continue.

## Verification

Run focused tests during implementation.
Run the complete command set in `AGENTS.md` before a push.
Use `.github/workflows/ci.yml` as the exact CI command source.
Run the four mutation-diff shards for a release candidate.
Keep the observational mutation result as residual evidence.
Do not claim that a skipped or failed gate passed.

Use an external trust root for signature verification.
Do not let the candidate authenticate itself.

## Documentation

Use the project ASD-STE100 Issue 9 style.
Use short active sentences.
Put one instruction or topic in each sentence.
Use American English word forms.
Do not use contractions.

Do not use semicolons.
Define each abbreviation at first use.
Use one term for one concept.
Preserve exact technical data.
State the scope and evidence tier of each result.
State what each result does not prove.

## Collaboration and Git

Edit only assigned files during delegated work.
Do not merge, tag, publish, or change repository settings during delegated work.
The release operator must review each returned line.
The release operator must rerun decisive tests.

Commit one coherent verified milestone at a time.
Sign every commit.
Use Sepehr Mahmoudian as the sole commit author.
Use a concise professional imperative subject.
Do not add automated attribution or a co-author trailer.

Do not force-push `main`.
Push the accepted exact candidate to `origin/main`.

## Stop conditions

Stop if the candidate identity differs from the expected identity.
Stop if a signed input changed.
Stop if required evidence is missing.
Stop if a claim exceeds its evidence tier.
Stop if an edit creates a command or authority edge.

Stop if another agent owns the same file.
Resolve the condition before you continue.
